    summary:"Essential vitamin. Injectable form dramatically outperforms oral. Critical for nerves and energy.",
    description:`Vitamin B12 (Methylcobalamin) is an essential water-soluble vitamin that cannot be produced by the human body. Methylcobalamin is the active, directly usable form — superior to the cheaper cyanocobalamin in most supplements which requires conversion.

B12 is critical for DNA synthesis (cell division), myelin sheath formation (nerve insulation), and red blood cell production. Deficiency causes megaloblastic anemia, peripheral neuropathy, cognitive decline, and mood disorders.

The injectable advantage: oral B12 absorption depends on intrinsic factor (a protein made by the stomach). Many people — especially older adults, those with gut issues, or on metformin (diabetes drug) — have impaired intrinsic factor and absorb oral B12 poorly. Injectable bypasses this entirely, delivering 100% directly to tissues.

Methylcobalamin specifically has evidence for nerve repair — used in Japan for peripheral neuropathy because it supports Schwann cell function and myelin synthesis.

Essential for anyone on plant-based diets: B12 exists almost exclusively in animal products. Vegans/vegetarians are at high risk for deficiency.`,
