    description:`Snap-8 (Acetyl Glutamyl Heptapeptide-3) is an 8-amino acid peptide that works by the same principle as Botox — partially inhibiting the SNARE complex proteins (SNAP-25, syntaxin, synaptobrevin) needed for nerve-muscle communication.

Botox completely blocks SNARE complex formation by cleaving SNAP-25 with botulinum toxin — this completely paralyzes targeted muscles. Snap-8 partially competes for SNARE complex formation, reducing but not eliminating muscle contraction. The result: reduced expression lines without the complete paralysis of injectable Botox.

Clinical studies: Snap-8 at 10% concentration reduces expression wrinkle depth by approximately 26% compared to placebo over 28 days. Effects are cumulative with consistent daily use. Best results in forehead lines, crow's feet, and glabellar lines (frown lines).

Often combined with Argireline (a similar but shorter SNARE complex competitor) in multi-peptide anti-wrinkle serums for additive effects.`,
